comment.text:
Great menu with a wide variety of vegetarian, vegan and gluten free options; the coffee menu is also solid! Just a tad pricey... a relatively basic brunch cost around $35. That doesn't make the food any less delicious, but the pricing could be slightly more reasonable. 

It was pretty busy when I went and the service lagged a bit too. But again, the food was good enough to recommend and go back!

Wow what a find!  I really enjoyed my visit here.  I got the vegan breakfast sandwich and the vegan sausage balls.   My girlfriend got the waffle, chicken sausage and potatoes.   The potatoes were not great..she did not eat. I'm so glad I listened to the server.  I was going to get the vegan hash but she said the potatoes were different than their usual potatoes and people were not particularly fond of them.  My sandwich was delicious...I was confused about the sausage balls. I thought it was sausage stuffed beignets.  That was my bad for not reading.  It was still ok though.  The waffle was super good. I need gluten free but I still tried it.  I'm not sure if they have gluten free waffles but next time I may still get it. 

Now my only feedback is my girlfriend got the potatoes because the other choice was Johnny cake.  She didn't get johnnycake because who needs waffles and corn cakes.  Little did we know they are calling hash brown Johnny cake. The server was like yes people often assume it's pancake.  People are not assuming...that's what they are. Can you tell I really feel a way about this? 

The place itself is beautiful though. Really nicely decorated.  Lots of seating. Can't wait until warm weather the outside seating on the side looks cozy.

The food was so good and the atmosphere is amazing 
I ordered the chicken sandwich with fries and coffee 
And got a waffle 
My niece had avocado toast 
The service was great everyone was friendly 
I will definitely go back when I'm in Atlanta

photos.caption: French toast ,chicken waffle and the avocado toast
The chicken waffle and the pickled Okra was so yummy

comment.text:
Another week, another breakfast/brunch review. First off let me start off by saying I love the way this restaurant is laid out there are 2 different sides you can choose to sit from, and they are completely different the dichotomy of the restaurant is cool. I went on a Monday morning and it was pretty empty, just a few people that were working on laptops; which this is a solid work/study spot.

I ordered the waffle BLT. The waffle and the bacon were both amazing. The only issue I found is that waffle doesn't make for a proper substitute for bread. The waffle was so crumbly so I made a giant mess lol. Next time I'll order the waffle and bacon separate. Also this place has some of the best I've ever had in my life. 

I'll definitely be back. You're welcome!

For the breakfast plate you can customize it with the way you want your eggs cooked, additional choice of protein, and choice of grits or hash browns (I think). Solid portions. Only complaint is biscuit was a little dry and/or overcooked. While I didn't try the goat cheese croquettes, my friends enjoyed them and said they were very rich. They are a pretty decent size too. 

Nice space and lots of people studying/working from there. You order through the toast app so makes it easy if paying separately and then it's brought out to you.

Love the atmosphere here! It's so amazingly clean, the staff is absolutely fabulous, nice decor and marble and wood tables. 

Great location off Howell Mill Road. 

Best waffles. Real maple syrup! Real butter!

I decided to get a change of scenery and work somewhere new today. Cultivate was the perfect place! I went there for breakfast and ordered J's sandwich (added cheddar cheese) and the heirloom and avocado. The sandwich was good, but a little dry. The tomato and avocado were ok, but needed seasoning. The service was pretty good. Great work environment!
Love this place. The ambiance is super cute and the service is good. I love how there are so many gluten free options! The matcha was the best matcha i've ever had!!!

Amazing little breakfast spot on the west side. It's a little hard to get in and out of because Howell Mill has awful traffic, but at least there is a parking lot.
When we arrived for breakfast, the line was out the door. I didn't have high expectations, but the line moved very efficiently and they even have someone stationed near the register to help you find a table, which is amazing.
I loved my breakfast biscuit--it was just the right side and tasted great. Our coffees were also tasty. I'll definitely return.

photos.caption: Strawberry Cream Cheese Waffle Farm Fresh Bacon

comment.text:
Cultivate had four stars on average when I saw it, and the menu looked so good so I had to come find out why it wasn't a five out of five! 

First of all, the interior is super cute and welcoming. It is quite well decorated. There's plenty of seating and the tables are large enough to even whip out your laptop, which I saw several folks doing. And I love the whole order and pay from your phone situation. It's the efficiency for me. 

I ordered the oat milk cinnamon honey latte with an extra shot of espresso. It was too sweet for me, be the presentation was nice and the temperature was perfect. I'd give it an 8 out of 10. 

The beignets were the biggest disappointment. I just knew I was going to get some fluffy New Orleans beignets. Absolutely not.  The flavor was there, but the texture was not. It was way too dense and not light and airy like an authentic beignet. I think the issue is that they made it gluten-free...I'd give it a 3 out of 10. I didn't even finish the one I bit into. But the two sauces they served it with were delicious. My friend actually liked them, she said they're good for "vegan and gluten free" and that I shouldn't expect an authentic taste lol

The vegan breakfast sandwich was actually super flavorful and I enjoyed the jam. From a culinary perspective, it needed some plants...like lettuce, avocado, or something to lighten it up. I'd give it an 8 out of 10. The vegan breakfast sausage was one of the best I've ever had. 

My friend ordered the build your own breakfast bowl and she LOVED it and vowed to go back for it again tomorrow. She was impressed with every bite through and through. She's give it a 10 out of 10. 

Overall, I'd definitely come back but not for the latte and not for the beignets.

Had the best matcha ice latte at Cultivate Food and Coffee this morning! This establishment is an entire vibe serving up delicious food and wonderful service! 

I was in a bit of a hurry so I ordered to go. The staff placed my order for me and within 15 minutes my food was packed up neatly! 

This was my first visit, but definitely won't be my last!

Our favorite new brunch spot in Atlanta! We cannot wait to come back next week. Due to food allergies, I unfortunately have to eat dairy-free & gluten-free which is really hard to follow when eating out. I was so happy to not only find a restaurant with several GF/DF options, but with DELICIOUS options! Everything we ordered was incredible. GF/V breakfast sandwich (eggs and cheese tasted real!) with a pork sausage patty instead of vegan - so, so good. The GF sausage balls were to dieee for and so was the peach pepper jelly and blueberry compote on the side. He ordered the chicken biscuit with the pimento cheese and the Nashville hot sauce on the side. Best hot sauce I've ever had, I dipped everything in it. The potato Johnny cakes were also amazing. The sriracha bacon was good, but probably won't order next time (flimsy even though we asked for extra crispy and just 2 pieces, but good flavor!) Loved the atmosphere, coffee was great, and our waiter was super sweet!

This a fantastic spot to come for a quick breakfast. They get crowded on the weekends, so be prepared for that. They have a great menu that will make it hard to decide what you want to eat. I enjoyed my food so much here that I came back again the next day. The cooks are amazing here they make perfect eggs and grits. Those are two items that many places can't even cook correctly.

photos.caption: Waffle with strawberries and cream cheese
This Pomegranate Green Tea was amazing
Grit bowl with sausage and eggs on top.

comment.text:
I love it here! The culinary adventure at this establishment was nothing short of exceptional. The salmon hash, expertly cultivated, proved to be a gastronomic masterpiece that demands a try for any enthusiast. Equally impressive was the chicken sandwich, a harmonious blend of flavors that left a lasting impression.

The staff's accommodation, evident in their willingness to split meals for sharing, added a touch of warmth to the dining experience. Noteworthy was the turmeric golden milk, a refreshing and amazing beverage that complemented the meal perfectly.

The attentiveness of both the bar and service staff contributed to the overall positive ambiance. Whether patrons were engrossed in work or leisurely enjoying their day, the atmosphere proved accommodating for both pursuits.

With plans to explore the entire menu on subsequent visits, including the extensive cocktail selection, the prospect of returning is met with anticipation. The establishment's commitment to culinary excellence and a diverse menu, coupled with attentive service and great ambiance, makes it a definite go-to for future dining endeavors. They also offer military discounts!

Cultivate was on my Atlanta bucket list for a LONGGG time. As of this review, I have now been here two times. Once for my birthday and once in April. It's a beautiful atmosphere and very friendly staff. 

From the drink menu, I've had both the Lavender Matcha Green Latte and the Golden Latte. Their signature drinks are some of the most unique I've found, on par with East Pole Coffee Co...

From the food options, I've tried the Bacon Pimento Cheese Waffle and the Cultivate Chicken Biscuit (which I believe is what is pictured). 

Next time I will have to try the shrimp & grits, I tend to order that at every brunch place I visit to compare.

owner_replies.comment: Megan, thank you so much for your feedback! We are so glad you love Cultivate as much as we do and we are so excited to see you again soon!

comment.text:
Amazing place! I have seen videos of Cultivate on the weekend and it looks very busy. I went on a Friday with a friend and there wasn't a wait.
It isn't a normal restaurant situation, it's where you can sit down at a table, scan a code to the Toast app to order and then a waiter will deliver the food to your table. You can also pay through the app which means you can leave whenever you want.
The space is nice, airy, and clean with amazing food. I highly recommend this place (maybe during the week so you aren't waiting a long time). 
Also the servers are so nice!! They helped to explain the process and checked in to see if we were ok throughout our meal.

photos.caption: BYO Brunch Sandwich with veggie sausage
Cultivate Chicken Sandwich with a mimosa
The whole set up where you can help yourself to condiments and water

comment.text:
Cultivate is a solid breakfast spot off of Howell Mill Rd. The location is off of a busy street and it could be easy to miss if you don't know which side of the street to look for it on.

Parking
There is a small parking lot with free spaces. If that's full, there is a parking garage just across the back street.

Seating
PLENTY of seating. Where you are looking for solo to mid size group seating, you can find a spot. They have both indoor and outdoor seating that ranges from booths to standalone tables and high top to low top tables.

Menu
Great size menu that accomodates all good choices. If you're vegan or gluten free there really is something for everyone here. 

Food
I chose the build your own breakfast sandwich (bacon and egg on croissant bread). My sandwich was great and I really loved the croissant bread they offered. Ordering was annoying. They only offer a digital menu and you order and pay via your phone. Personally, I don't like this restaurant trend. I had questions about the menu but didn't have anyone to ask. 

Service
Walking in I was immediately greeted which is always appreciated. Once we ordered, servers brought out our food and that was the last we saw of them. I would've liked a water or condiment for my sandwich but again, no one to ask for either of those things. No one even came over to make sure our food came out as preferred.

When you order your food, you receive a text notifying you that you've begun a tab, and another text reminding you to check out/close your tab. I was meeting a colleague and really wanted to focus on the conversation and spend time away from my phone. I don't like that this restaurant really makes the patron depend on their phone for the entire experience. My only reason for giving 4 stars, instead of 5, is the phone dependency.

I've been to Cultivate when it first opened, and then again later on and used to dream about their chicken and waffles. They were so good!!

I was so disappointed when I went recently! Their waffle was way smaller than before, not crispy or particularly flavorful. The chicken was also very dry and cold. They even forgot my husbands order altogether and we had to ask for the second order to be made, which took another 35-45 min (so we shared mine while waiting for his). 

It seems like people know it too, because it's not nearly as crowded as it used to be. Really sad!

owner_replies.comment:
Good afternoon Huma, 
What a pleasant surprise to read your encouraging and detailed review! 
We are so thankful you enjoyed your time with us and we will see you the next time you are here! 

See you soon:)

comment.text:
Came here for some coworking the other day and really loved it! 

***PARKING*** 
There are a few free spots right outside, but if not there are more free spots in the parking garage a few steps away! 

***ATMOSPHERE***
The atmosphere was so nice! It was very bright and clean and had several other people working on laptops. I loved that you order from your phone directly at the table so anytime while you are working you can just order or order something else! 

***STAFF***
The staff was super friendly and brought out everything so quickly! 

***FOOD/DRINKS***
So good! I just had an iced dirty chaga and it was 10/10! Also had grits with normal cheddar and they were so yum! 

They have Soo many vegan and gluten free choices! I love that! I also love that you can sub the vegan options for non vegan. The grits were listed as vegan but you can choose your cheese so I opted for dairy cheddar :) everything is very customizable though which is great for all diets! 

***PRICE***
Pretty normal for a nicer cafe in Atl! My drink was 8.50 I believe so slightly on the more expensive end but it was reasonable for what it was. It had espresso and milk like any latte but also a superfood powder etc. So I think the price was okay. It was also soo good! The grits were 5$ which is really not much and they were very filling! 

***CONCLUSION***
Definitely will be back here soon!!

The one thing I love most about visiting Atlanta is that there is NO SHORTAGE of restaurants to try. So, like many times prior, I got a chance to try a restaurant that had been on my list of venues to visit for some time now, thanks to my best friend. And, thankfully, Cultivate did NOT disappoint. 

I had the strawberries and cream cheese waffles with a side of biscuit, and two espresso martinis - which, for a typically non-coffee drinker like myself were OUTSTANDINGLY delicious!! The price point was great. Everything was fresh and prepared in a timely manner. The staff was amazing and the overall aesthetic and atmosphere of the establishment was really good. 

Overall, I would go back time and time over and recommend to anybody looking for a great brunch / breakfast spot.

photos.caption: Strawberry Cream Cheese Waffle, Buttermilk Biscuit, & Espresso Martinis

comment.text:
Came in for brunch this past Monday around 9:30.  It was MLK day so I think it was a bit more crowded than a typical Monday. You order at the counter and then find a table. It wasn't too crowded when we got there, but by the time we left at 11, people were waiting for tables. 
The food took a while to arrive, but it was quite tasty. My friend got a matcha latte. I just got black coffee. She loved the matcha latte! For food, we got the brunch sandwich and the eggs Benedict. I got the sandwich and got it as a biscuit with eggs, bacon and cheese. It also came with a little (very little) side of jam. My friends eggs Benedict was interesting. It was served on a biscuit. The biscuits were pretty good. They are big. I wish they gave more jam. Overall pretty good. They have a big menu with lots of vegetarian and vegan options as well.

owner_replies.comment: Carlie, thank you so much for your feedback and photos. We're so glad you enjoyed our unique menu items and look forward to Cultivating Kindness with you again soon :)

comment.text:
This place is so nasty. The vegan breakfast sandwich same sopping wet and completely unseasoned. There was not a SPEC of salt or pepper much less any other seasoning. The beignets are RAW!!!! I literally tore one open and it was completely filled with RAW dough! Not to mention even if they were cooked they are extremely dense and are not actual light, fluffy beignets. Oh, and let's not forget the fact that the server totally ignored us. Don't waste your money here.

EDITED TO ADD: I got food poisoning. Yep.

I was just here for a meeting and the staff was warm and welcoming!

Parking can be a little difficult as parking might seem limited like parking in front of their store or in the parking garage. However, their service says other wise because they made sure to check up on us to see if we needed anything and made sure we had a great experience! 

The coffee their was delicious and loved the idea of building your own through their website or link from their QR code. I was able to either check out or open a tab if I was staying there for a good amount of time. It was great! I had both their cappuccino and latte, which both were rich in flavor and made me want to get another by I had to hold back my temptation.

photos.caption: Cappuccino (Double Shot with Almond Milk and Caramel)

owner_replies.comment: Coleton, thank you so much for the positive feedback! We are so glad you enjoyed our hand-roasted coffee, Order and Pay system, and friendly service. We hope to see you again soon to Cultivate Kindness!

comment.text:
We got here just before noon and it was the perfect timing. Wait time was average for the season and type of location. 
The cashier was amazing and patient with me as I asked my many questions , come to find out I had some "credit " under my number ! And got $50 off so the whole meal was FREE! 
The atmosphere was great too! 
I encourage you if coming with someone to jus have someone take a menu and find a place to sit and text the person in line what they want as seating May be the issue. 
They bring you the food to your table and are super helpful if you need anything. 
Parking however is also an issue because of the location, however I give it 5 stars because the service, the cleanliness , the taste, and the timeframe in which we got our food were all great ! 
Ev

owner_replies.comment: Omar, thank you so much for this feedback and for being a loyal guest! We so appreciate the photos and details of your experience. We hope to see you again soon to Cultivate more Kindness :)

comment.text:
Food: 9/10
Service: 10/10
Ambiance: 9/10

This brunch spot is cute! They are known for their Tea but unfortunately I dont drink tea. Not a bummer but I did try their cold drinks. I ordered the Salmon Hash as pictured. It was really good, the food came out hot and the cream cheese on top was an amazing add. The portion of the food was great, (i took some to go) I had a Lemonade 8oz with Delta 8 in it. (You can taste it) but it was still good and drinkable. 
The service is a new kind of service that i am starting to see now. You walk in, you can sit anywhere. Each table has a virtual menu for you to scan. With the virtual scan it allows you to place your order online and add a card at the same time to be convenient. Once placed my order the waiter came to bring it out in no time and once finished, you can get up n go since your check was already covered! Brilliant!

owner_replies.comment: Simone, thank you so much for this detailed feedback! We are so glad you enjoyed our unique menu items, new ordering format, and the overall ambiance and culture of Cultivate. We hope to see you again soon!

comment.text:
What an awesome place to work and spend some time! 

As one who works from home, I love nothing more than designating a few days out of my week/month to work out of the home whenever the vibes feel right. With my pilates studio not being too far, stumbling upon Cultivate via Yelp has been one of my fave new remote working opportunities. 

Upon arrival, parking in the public garage just steps away was such a breeze. When I walked in, I just felt totally refreshed by the bright and open interiors. With large windows that are almost ceiling to floor, and their colorfully tiled floors, I just fell in love at first sight. I grabbed a table in the corner and got cozy quickly. I hadn't been paying attention to the availability of electrical outlets but lucky me, as soon as I turned around in my seat, boom! An outlet :) (With a super cute, cheeky sign lol) 

With QR codes displayed on the tables guiding guests to their caffeinated cravings, ordering was a breeze. I actually love the option of ordering via an app from my table, especially when I'm working as I may be sitting there for 4 hours and going through numerous drinks and snacks. I ended up going with a few Salted Caramel Lattes on my first visit paired with a BYO Vegan Grit Bowl.  DELICIOUS. All of it. They were brought out fresh by the awesome Cultivate team and I was excited to see them coming with each new order. I almost stayed long enough to close my laptop and enjoy some cocktails, but decided to save that for another day. 

If you're looking for a new coffee shop, a spot for smoothies, or delicious place for lunch and more - Cultivate is worth a try!

photos.caption: Great place to work at for the day!
I got someone else's plate and realized once I snapped this lol but, yum!
BYO Vegan Grit Bowl with avocado, peppers & onions, bacon and eggs

owner_replies.comment: Erica, thank you so much for your positive feedback and beautiful photos. We hope to see you again soon!

comment.text:
I came here for breakfast and coffee in between meetings and immediately loved the location. Very spacious and clean with a lot of beautiful natural light coming through and great relaxing music.

I got a cappuccino with almond milk which was perfectly made, and the west side plate which came with eggs, bacon, a croissant, a Johnny cake, and I added season fruit as well. It's a bit pricey, but trust me when I say it's a FULL plate of food, super delicious, and in my opinion worth it. The staff weee all very friendly and helpful as well

This is definitely one of the best spots for a vegan breakfast. Also, the coffee is absolutely amazing along with the lavender lemonade my mom got. I had got the west side plate, which was pretty good and the French toast as well but I'd say the star of the show was the vegan grit dish. My mom got that dish but I plan to come back and get that myself and then to try the salmon dish one day too. I also got a hot drink made iced but forgot the name of it and it was really good. I'll have to come back and do a review again for the name of the drink. This place is definitely worth going to. 
Park in the parking garage if you can and dining is mainly self serve. The ambiance is a very chill one which is nice.

photos.caption: French Toast with Lemon Whipped Ricotta

owner_replies.comment: Michelle, reviews like yours are so encouraging! Thank you so much for the positive feedback and nice photos. We're so glad you enjoyed our Salmon Bowl, Lavender Lemonade, and hand roasted coffee! We look forward to seeing you at Cultivate again soon :)

comment.text:
I've been here twice. There's a small parking lot, some parallel parking spaces and a deck available, but one time all were completely full so we had to wait for sometime to leave  Both times, seating was a challenge. You'll wait in line to order, both times there were maybe 10-15 folk ahead of us and the area for the line is pretty small and adjacent to the entry so it gets tight. After you order, you're hustling to find a seat, like any seat. I don't love the feeling of ordering to eat in and not knowing that you'll be able to sit somewhere to eat -akin to a fast food setup.

The first time the food was good. I ordered salmon hash both times. They offer a very light, healthy menu with vegan/vegetarian options. The first time, the salmon hash was lovely. The second time they bought it without capers and with no sauce. Either they mixed up my order or the kitchen was too hurried and my server didn't notice. When I bought it to her attention, instead of taking my plate to correct it, she merely bought a cup of capers and a cup of sauce. Ultimately it did not taste as well as the first time. A great segway to the service. Most of the servers appear under 30 and are generally nonchalant in spirit. Some are friendly or pretend to be. Others don't try much. Expect truly marginal service here. Maybe it's because folk may not tip since you have to order and seat yourself. No clue but my second visit was damaged enough that I'll skip this place in the future. The food was not good enough to suffer poor service.

owner_replies.comment: Brenda, we so appreciate your feedback! I'm so sorry that your last visit was not up to par and we are in the process of switching back to full-service (should be 100% full service by June) and we have new menu offerings so we hope to see you again soon for a new experience!

comment.text:
Run, don't walk! This place is fire! It's got a variety of options on the menu. Super tasty, fresh and unique flavors. 

Coffee was amazing and so are their smoothies! 

Do yourself a favor and frequent this spot to work your way through the menu. 

The line can get long for brunch, but it moves quick so don't let it discourage you! Staff is super attentive as well. Decor is super cute too.  Great spot for taking pics for the gram.

Chicken on menu is halal. We ordered the French toast , breakfast bowl with chicken, vanilla latte and house coffe. The bowl was great although the French toast was hard and not sweet. Coffee was nice, vanilla latte was not the best. It's more of a self serve (drink refill, napkins, utensils) which for some is ideal, especially for me since I like to have enough napkins, but you tip when you initially ordered and I suppose the service was not there especially considering you help yourself to majority of the tasks. Our bill came out to $65 with tax. For the quality and the amount, I don't think it's worth it.

This place is great!

MENU AND DRINKS
For startes, this place is pricy, but it's totally worth it. There are a lot of food, coffee and drink options to choose from. We ordered a capuccino, a dirty chaga, the cultivate benedict and the cultivate bowl. They were all delicious and sizable, so if you like big meals, this is your place.

LOCATION AND PARKING
Cultivate is in a nice and centrally located area in Atlanta. There is free parking outside and there is also a residential shared parking garage within walking distance. 

VIVE
The design is beautiful and modern with a lot of natural lighting.

WHAT TO WORK ON
Some of the table products, such as ketchup, sweeteners, etc. have high fructose corn syrup and natural flavors.

Overall, we loved our first experience here, and we can't wait to come back!

owner_replies.comment: José, thank you so much for this amazing feedback! We look forward to seeing you at Cultivate again soon.

comment.text:
My wife and I went there on a mid morning Sunday. It was quite busy when we got there but we were seated within 15 minutes. The food was amazing; everything tasted so good and fresh. The standout thing was their customer service. Every few minutes someone showed up to our table asking if we needed anything. When we had an issue with one of our dishes, they let us keep it and gave us another item on the house. 

I would go there again indefinitely just for the exceptional customer service.

Such a cute spot for brunch! Lots of seating and our food came out relatively fast. I ordered the vegan and gf brunch sandwich which was surprisingly really good! I'm not vegan or gf but occasionally opt for the no meat option. It was barely detectable that this sandwich is vegan and gluten free! The sandwhich was so flavorful and filling! I love a good sweet/salty combo and the side of blueberry compote that came with it meshed wonderfully with the sandwich! My friend ordered a cultivate-a-sandwhich with a bagel, bacon, and eggs. She said it was quite good. We also ordered coffee- the highlight of the meal! The blue nectar latte was my favorite! Definitely not your typical coffee, but it tasted great and looks stunning! The oat milk and honey latte was solid too. Overall, I would recommend! Great food but even better coffee!

photos.caption: Vegan Brunch Sandwich (front) & cultivate Cultivate a Sandwich (back- bagel bacon eggs)
Oat Milk & Honey Iced Espresso & Blue Nectar Latte

comment.text: Loved the build your own bowl with Kale, vegan sausage, and vegan egg. Lavender Matcha was good as well.

photos.caption: Build your own bowl with vegan eggs and Vegan Sausage Patties

comment.text:
Free parking in the back. We went during brunch- it was delicious! The check was about $50 for two.

You stand in line to order your food and bring a number to your table for them to bring the food to. Kind of like Jason's Deli. Tables are first come first serve. 

Pros:
Great ambiance! Seating inside and outside. Very chill, comfy, and relaxing. This is a great alternative to the loud and crowded brunch venues we have in downtown Atlanta.

I had the shrimp and grits. () The Cajun sauce was not too spicy and the shrimp were fresh.

Cons: 
The place itself is a little hard to find. There isn't a huge sign you can see from the street but there is one on the building. It is not very big and the writing is in black.

Would I Recommend: Yes, anyday.

Follow me @jessreviewss on Instagram for more

owner_replies.comment: Jessye, thanks so much for your positive feedback! We look forward to seeing you again soon.

comment.text: Nice back patio. Food was delicious and cute ambiance. Thank you to Sierra for the recommendations and good energy!

Service: parking wasn't as bad as others mentioned. The garage has people constantly moving in and out. 
You stand in a line to order- which is fine.. but then you have to wait to be seated, even when plenty of spots are available. 
Food: the proteins are great. Everything was hot and fresh. The beignets and waffles are super dense and was more like a cake donut, than light and fluffy. 
Ambiance was great. It's a cool brunch spot or day date. Would be back to try alternatives from the menu. 
Best items are definitely their drink selection. The lemonades and teas are delicious.

Cultivate is the perfect place to grab brunch and coffee with friends, family, or solo; lots of menu items for different diets. When they first opened a few years ago they had traditional waitress service and I believe you also had the option to make a reservation. Well things are much different; on a busy Sunday I had to wait in a very long line to place an order, then I received a number. Seriously, this placed was packed on a Sunday around 11am, fortunately my sister and I were able to find a table for two. Once your items are ready a server brings them to your table, which is why you're provided a number.
 
On this visit in mid-February, I dined with my sister. We shared an order of vegan sausage balls ($15), vegan beignets ($12), and mimosa bucket ($30). I ordered a vegan brunch sandwich for my entrée ($18). I also had an oat milk lavender latte which was close to $7
 
We both enjoyed our meal and had a really good time. It took a very long time for our food to come out to us, so this is not the spot to come to if you're short on time; we gave ourselves two hours for dining at the restaurants, however that still wasn't' enough time due to the long food wait. I'm sure they probably were short staffed, and I know the food is made to order but it still was longer than expected. It would be nice if you're given an estimate of when your food will arrive to the table after you pay.  
 
Vegan Sausage Balls - think meatballs! You get about 5 and it's served with peach pepper jelly and blueberry compote.
Beignets - are gluten free and vegan so don't expect NOLA style. You get about 6 served with maple syrup and a seasonal dipping sauce.
Vegan sandwich - very filling, I was only able to eat half. It's a vegan patty, chao cheese, and vegan egg inside of vegan bread.
Mimosa bucket - serves four people and you get three different juices to go with your champagne.
 
There is a small lot with a few parking spaces, then there is garage parking. The day I visited it was completely full, so I went to the overflow parking lot next to McDonalds.
 
Overall enjoyed my meal and would return, my preference would be on a weekday over a weekend to avoid the crowds.

owner_replies.comment: Kaneka, thank you so much for your feedback! We really appreciate the time you took to share details of your experience. We look forward to Cultivating more Kindness with you soon.

comment.text:
Cute place!  Love the decor and the uplifting quotes on the walls.  It gives a very welcoming feel.  

The food was fresh and served fairly quickly after ordering.  Thankfully, we arrived before the line started to form.  It's a quick service restaurant so you order at the counter and they deliver it to your table.  Likely a great place for people watching or meeting up with friends.

Came here with a group of 8 for Sunday brunch. There are no reservations. You stand in line & order at the counter. We waited about 30 minutes. Then it's a free for all trying to get a table. There is seating outside, but obviously the weather has to be cooperating...

Lots of good vegan options, including the beignets (which are also gluten free). Great espresso drinks & boozy brunch drinks.

owner_replies.comment: Virginia, thank you so much for your feedback! We are so glad your group enjoyed our handcrafted espresso drinks, cocktails, and beignets. Sunday tends to be one of our busiest days and we hope to see you again soon to Cultivate Kindness.

comment.text:
It's January 1, 2024 and I am saddened to begin the year describing my embarrassing and humiliating and extremely bad experience at Cultivate Food and Coffee on Howell Mill Road.  

I've passed this establishment hundreds of times throughout my commute around Atlanta. I woke up this New Year's Day wanting coffee and brunch. 

Before I begin, let me first say that this restaurant is very nice, clean and modern with an artistic, yet sophisticated feel.  The food presentation is amazing and the atmosphere seemed warm and inviting.  HOWEVER, despite the ambiance, and the extremely well prepared presentation of the food, the management (Kylie) displayed a VERY DIFFERENT experience than what I hoped!

My first experience was one that involved me feeling embarrassment, humiliation and disgust. My encounter was beyond disbelief with the manager of the establishment named Kylie. Kylie was offensive, prejudicial and lacked professional judgment. I'm not sure if her lack of professional judgment was the result of her inexperience as a manager, or if it was the result of prejudice, racism, and deep rooted anger, or maybe lack of self-esteem and attention in her personal life. 

Whatever caused her publicly inappropriate comments to 
me, it was certainly enough to make me question if I would ever come back into this establishment again.

I been trying to get here since they opened and sadly I was mildly disappointed. I came here on a Saturday for a late breakfast, around 1. There's limited parking right up against the building and then a shared parking deck further down. You stand in line to order. They have traditional menus and QR codes. Once you place your order at the register, you seat yourself.

They have high tops, bench seating and traditional tables.  There's plenty of seating and the atmosphere was very chill. I liked it. The drinks were super yummy. We ordered the turmeric latte and the honey latte. The food on the other hand left much to be desired.  The food came out fairly quickly. We got the salmon hash and the nashville hot chicken and waffle.  The salmon hash was ok but the dish overall lacked seasoning. The hot chicken and waffle was a major miss. The "hot chicken" sauce tasted more like general tso's chicken and the waffle was meh. As someone who lives part time in Nashville, I definitely would not call that "Nashville Hot."  For this to be my first time here, the food did not deliver.

owner_replies.comment: Shantrell, we so appreciate your feedback! Thank you for the kind words about Cultivate's atmosphere and handcrafted drinks! We're glad you finally got the chance to come visit and we would love to see you again soon.

comment.text:
i loooove the vibes here! parking is rough and waiting in line takes a long time especially for weekend brunch but o once you make it to the counter and your seat, it is a lovely experience.

the vegan food here is sooo on point - you can have your health kick or choose greasy and buttery brunch. the vegan sausage is kinda too salty but overall the food is veryyy goot

A couple logistics to know: No reservations. You order at the counter, grab a number and pick a seat. There was a pretty long line but lots of seating available and the line went pretty quick. 

The Goat Cheese Croquettes were my favorite! Awesome crust filled with goat cheese. It also come with dipping sauces that are seasonal. One was super sweet, the other kind of spicy so it was a nice mix. The Cultivate Benedict wasn't on the QR code menu for some reason but it's on the main menu. The biscuits were super flaky, but the pork belly was a tad dry. Overall, still an interesting dish, but not the best bennys I've ever had. My husband got the French Toast. I wasn't a fan of the multigrain toast, but ricotta added some good flavor. I also was not a fan of the Lavender Matcha Latte, but my husband loved it. It was wayyyyy to sweet for me, and you taste much more lavender than you do matcha. 

Overall, a great experience. There was outdoor and indoor seating. Seems to be a cool date spot or place to have a friend's brunch. I'd go back to try some of the other stuff on the menu (fried chicken looked delicious) and get the Croquettes again!

photos.caption: French Toast with Lemon Whipped Ricotta

owner_replies.comment: Nadia, thank you so much for the positive feedback! We're excited to see you at Cultivate again soon.

comment.text: I really enjoyed the food, vibe, and service at this place! Cute little coffee place with great, healthy options for brunch.  Get there early if you plan to go on a Saturday morning because it is fairly small and some use it as a co-working spot. We went at around 11:30 and let's just say we beat the crowd by about maybe 15 minutes. Literally, no line and then we look back behind us as we are being seated and the flood gates of brunchies  had arrived. Lol.  This place is worth trying for sure!
ALWAYS a hit!! 10/10 with good vegan/vegetarian options. I think i try something new every time i go. Service is ok, you order they give you a number but seating is first come first serve.

This place is great ! Parking is super easy - staff is friendly - ordering is easy- you order on your phone place the order and you're done - 
It's wonderful 

Coffee choices are excellent - 
Food choices are great - 
Liked the fried chicken sandwich 
The avocado toast with eggs 
And the Salmon wrap was also good -

owner_replies.comment: Asma, thank you so much for your kind words! We're so glad you enjoyed our coffee, avocado toast, salmon wrap, and more. We look forward to Cultivating Kindness with you again soon!

comment.text: Came here for the first with a group of friends for Sunday brunch. Considering the peak time, I was pleasantly surprised by how fast the line moved! We each ordered the cultivate bowl and I liked how many options were offered to customize. The potatoes were really crispy and well seasoned but my favorite had to be the Cajun sauce that complimented the bowl really well. The goat cheese croquettes were also good but I wish they had more flavor or that the jams had other flavors to cut the richness of the goat cheese. The coffee options were also great both the cappuccinos and the iced coffees too. Overall, I really liked the experience and will be back to try the other options available!

I was excited to try this place out before I went just by looking at their photos and Instagram page! I was SO happy to see they had so many unique vegan options!  so many amazing items to choose from! The only thing I didn't really like was that we didn't really have a waiter. You had to order from an app you scanned on the table, it was really weird and you weren't allowed to ask the waiter any questions. They only brought your food to you. I'm not sure if I like that new way of "computer dining". Other than that, the food was amazing and did not take long at all. I recommend this cute place to others!

owner_replies.comment: Izzy, thank you so much for your feedback and beautiful photos! We're so glad you enjoyed dining with us and I love that our social media made you extra excited to come see us. We hope to see you again soon :)
